{"word":"ἐσσύμενος","slug":"ἐσσύμενος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐσσύμενος</b></el> <el>(ἐσσύμενος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> of <a href='S:σεύω'><el>σεύω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>hurrying, vehement, eager, impetuous</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:— <i>eager, yearning for</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἐσσῠμένως</el>, <i>hurriedly, furiously</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}